abstract: >
  Darwin Scaffold Studio is an open-source Julia platform for analyzing tissue
  engineering scaffolds from MicroCT and SEM imaging data. Features include:
  porosity measurement (<1% error), pore size analysis (1.4% error with Feret
  diameter), Physics-Informed Neural Networks (PINNs) for nutrient transport,
  Topological Data Analysis (TDA) with persistent homology, Graph Neural
  Networks (GNN) for property prediction, SAM3 segmentation, and OBO Foundry
  ontology integration. Validated D = phi hypothesis: salt-leached scaffolds
  exhibit fractal dimension matching the golden ratio (D = 1.685).

